  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if fractional carbon dioxide laser treatment of a
      fresh wound at the time of surgery, decreases scar formation. Scar revision is commonly done
      at 6-10 weeks following surgery. Therefore, it may be more beneficial, for both the patient
      and physician, to perform scar revision at the time of surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
